        <p data-uuid="13e9c8c7d20b4f1e9eb7d10a12ab0afc">Taylor’s success made him a war hero back home. He became known as “Old Rough and Ready” because of his enthusiasm to work side by side with his men. The general’s popularity troubled President Polk because the next presidential race was approaching. When Taylor’s progress stalled, Polk gave the command to General Winfield Scott. </p>
        <section class="historical-source nobg" data-uuid="b1f0680fc7be4f0d8d9d9fa31af9e9fe">
